.SH NAME
doc_usecases_integration_UC_end_user_md \- Use Case: Libelektra Configuration for End Users 
 
.SH "Summary"
.PP
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fBScope:\fP End User Configuration
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fBLevel:\fP Kite
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fBActors:\fP End User, System Administrator
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fBBrief:\fP End user customizes application settings using the configuration interface provided by Libelektra, enabling them to tailor the application to their preferences\&.
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fBStatus:\fP Draft
.PP
.SH "Scenarios"
.PP
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fBPrecondition:\fP Application has been developed with Libelektra integrated for configuration management and provides a user-friendly interface for end users to modify settings\&.
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fBMain success scenario:\fP End user successfully modifies application settings using the provided interface, leading to an improved user experience tailored to their preferences\&.
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fBAlternative scenario:\fP End user encounters issues while trying to modify settings, requiring them to seek assistance from support or refer to help documentation\&.
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fBError scenario:\fP End user's modifications lead to unintended behavior or conflicts in the application, requiring either the end user or system administrator to resolve the issue\&.
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fBPostcondition:\fP Application settings have been modified by the end user, resulting in a customized user experience\&.
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fBNon-functional Constraints:\fP
.IP "  \(bu" 4
Usability: The configuration interface should be user-friendly and easy to navigate for end users\&.
.IP "  \(bu" 4
Flexibility: Libelektra should support a wide range of configuration options and settings to cater to various end user preferences\&.
.IP "  \(bu" 4
Robustness: The configuration system should be robust and capable of handling potential conflicts or errors caused by end user modifications\&. 
.PP

.PP

